reviews.name: Shirley L.
reviews.review: I will use Parkme every time I need to go anywhere where there is little paring and a high density of people. There was no hunting for a spot, no running back and forth to fill the meter, wasting valuable vacation time, or spending more $ than intended just to park. Parkme made our trip easier and hassle-free. The only problem we did experience was trying to get out of the structure. The machine would not read our scan code, no matter how many times we tried. Were had to try to find someone who worked there to let us out. If I had not printed put the entire email showing enter and exit times, or had access to my email I would have had to pay the "lost ticket" price.

reviews.name: F U.
reviews.review: If I could leave negative stars I would!  In the stressful environment we are in given Covid, the worst Fires ever,  the angry divisiveness everywhere, and unemployment; I mistakenly went to the dentist to pick up invoices and I forgot my wallet (something I NEVER do).  I had already pulled into the newly automated garage before I realized it.  I was in the garage for a total of $3.  I hit the intercom twice in the space of 10 minutes until the attendant finally, and slowly, and begrudgingly walked to my car.  By then, it was $6.  I explained the situation and he said "so"... and despite how I tried to assure him, there was zero compassion or understanding, AT ALL.  I said can I leave you something so you believe that I'll come right back from my home, close by, and he said "what will you give me".  UNBELIEVABLE! He wanted my Apple phone.  I re-parked and went back up to the dental office who very kindly gave me a full day pass. He was THE MOST unhelpful, UNKIND individual that I've met in 6 months during the Quarantine and even for a long time before that.  That's saying something since I'm a lawyer and meet disgruntled people all the time..  I mean come on!!!  I was glad he was missing because I had to restrain myself from yelling as I drove out.   HIs name was "Alex" and he challenged me when I asked for his last name.  Yikes....no need to email me.  Neither I or any of my my local friends who live around the garage will park there ever again, once I share this story.
